CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 13, 1971, page 23 reads: "RECEIVING LINE-Wearing her gorgeous inaugural gown, a Malcolme Starr original, the Hon. C DeLores Tucker, Secretary of the Commonwealth of Pennsylvania, stands in receiving line at the recent reception given in her honor by the Women's Auxiliary of the Pittsburgh Branch NAACP. Held in the Terrace Room of the William Penn Hotel..." --Harris photo
TitMainTitle: Men, including one wearing dashiki and matching cap, and women, shaking hands with C. DeLores Tucker and others, in William Penn Hotel
